cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

The paper introduces a new recurrent neural network architecture for sequence modelling, which is a common topic in machine learning and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses empirical results on language modelling tasks, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-categories.
